dr.geo.contouring
Class ContourGenerator

java.lang.Object
  dr.geo.contouring.ContourGenerator

public class ContourGenerator
extends java.lang.Object

An object used to generate a list of contour lines or paths from a set of gridded three dimensional data.

Based on contour_plot.c from NeXTcontour1.4 by Thomas H. Pulliam, pulliam@rft29.nas.nasa.gov, MS 202A-1 NASA Ames Research Center, Moffett Field, CA 94035. I don't know how the original Fortran code looked like or where it came from, other than that NeXTcontour1.4 is based on Pieter Bunings' PLOT3D package for Computational Fluid Dynamics.

Ported from C to Java by Joseph A. Huwaldt, November 16, 2000.

Modified by: Joseph A. Huwaldt

Version:
November 23, 2000
Author:
Joseph A. Huwaldt Date: November 11, 2000, Marc Suchard

Constructor Detail

ContourGenerator

public ContourGenerator(double[][] xArr,
                        double[][] yArr,
                        double[][] fArr,
                        ContourAttrib[] cAttr)
Construct a ContourGenerator object using the specified data arrays and the specified attribute array. This constructor allows you to use data on an uneven X, Y grid.

Parameters:
xArr - 2D array containing the grid x coordinate data.
yArr - 2D array containing the grid y coordinate data.
fArr - 2D array containing the grid function (z) data.
cAttr - Array containing attributes of the contour levels.

ContourGenerator

public ContourGenerator(double[] xArr,
                        double[] yArr,
                        double[][] fArr,
                        ContourAttrib[] cAttr)
Construct a ContourGenerator object using the specified data arrays and the specified attribute array. This constructor allows you to use data on an evenly spaced grid where "X" values are invarient with "Y" and "Y" values are invarient with "X". This often occures where the data is on an evenly spaced cartesian grid.

Parameters:
xArr - 1D array containing the grid x coordinate data.
yArr - 1D array containing the grid y coordinate data.
fArr - 2D array containing the grid function (z) data.
cAttr - Array containing attributes of the contour levels.

ContourGenerator

public ContourGenerator(double[][] xArr,
                        double[][] yArr,
                        double[][] fArr,
                        int nc,
                        boolean logInterval)
Construct a ContourGenerator object using the specified data arrays. Contour attributes, including the interval, are generated automatically. This constructor allows you to use data on an uneven X, Y grid.

Parameters:
xArr - 2D array containing the grid x coordinate data.
yArr - 2D array containing the grid y coordinate data.
fArr - 2D array containing the grid function (z) data.
nc - The number of contour levels to generate.
logInterval - Uses a logarithmic contour interval if true, and uses a linear interval if false.

Method Detail

getContours

public ContourPath[] getContours()
                          throws java.lang.InterruptedException
Generate the contour paths and return them as an array of ContourPath objects. If there is a lot of data, this method method may take a long time, so be patient. Progress can be checked from another thread by calling "getProgress()".

Returns:
An array of contour path objects.
Throws:
java.lang.InterruptedException - if the user cancels this process (by calling "cancel()" from another thread).

done

public boolean done()
Returns true if the contour generation process is done. False if it is not.

cancel

public void cancel()
Call this method to cancel the generation of contours.

getProgress

public float getProgress()
Returns the progress of the currently executing contour generation process: 0.0 (just starting) to 1.0 (done).

private void computeContours()
                      throws java.lang.InterruptedException
Computes contour lines for gridded data and stores information about those contours. The result of this routine is a list of contour lines or paths.

Throws:
java.lang.InterruptedException

FlagContourPassings

private void FlagContourPassings()
Flag points in IA where the the function increases through the contour level, not including the boundaries. This is so we have a list of at least one point on each contour line that doesn't intersect a boundary.

accumContour

private void accumContour(int np,
                          int icont,
                          double[] x,
                          double[] y,
                          ContourAttrib cAttr)
Accumulate contour paths, as they are generated, into an overall list of contours.

Parameters:
np - The number of points in the contour path buffers.
icont - The index to the current contour level.
x,y - Buffers containing x & y coordinates of contour points.
cAttr - The attributes for this particular contour level.
